            <bio>
               <p>
                  <bold>Douglas R. Davis</bold>is an Associate Professor of Educational Leadership and Coordinator of Educational Leadership Programs, University of Mississippi. His main areas of expertise and research are teacher assessment and professional development, the preparation of educational leaders, and history and philosophy of education. Dr. Davis has published in many educational journals and has presented at over fifty scholarly and professional conferences. He is past editor of The Journal of Personnel Evaluation in Education and is past president of the Society of Philosophy and History of Education.</p>
            </bio>
